<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-05-0625 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Center was originally established for tasks in nuclear science andtechnology. Apart from the Fast Breeder Project, this comprises nuclearwaste management, nuclear safety, and the separation nozzle process foruranium enrichment. Recently, also non-nuclear projects have been started.Among these are environmental research which is expected to take up 20%of the Center's capacity in the long run, nuclear fusion, solid stateand materials research, and technology transfer. Karlsruhe Nuclear ResearchCenter carries out a number of projects on behalf of the Federal Governmentand the Land of Baden-Wuerttemberg.</TEXT></DOC>